{"questionId":"9067049","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Carbonated water is produced when carbon dioxide is dissolved in water under pressure.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">The following equilibria are established.</span></p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/a132676be95c32d44aa3a8ccb4df61a6253142f7.png\" width=\"517\" height=\"87\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Carbon dioxide acts as a weak acid.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">The hydrogencarbonate ion, produced in Equilibrium (2), can also act as an acid.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">State the formula of its conjugate base.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">CO<sub>3</sub><sup>2–</sup>&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9067049","referenceCode":"19M.2.sl.TZ2.a(ii)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"The hydrogencarbonate ion, produced in Equilibrium (2), can also act as an acid. State the formula of its conjugate base.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a(ii)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 8: Acids and bases","8.1 Theories of acids and bases","Core","Topic 8: Acids and bases"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}